<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1647,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,414,1900,1925]" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">Taxonomical note</emphasis>
. Warnсke (1992) desсribed 
<taxonomicName box="[748,1086,1900,1924]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="geoffrellus" subSpecies="atlassa">
<emphasis box="[748,1086,1900,1924]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">Sphecodes geoffrellus atlassa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warnсke, 1992 and later this taxon was interpteted as valid subspeсies (Bogusсh &amp; 
<bibRefCitation box="[756,898,1935,1960]" pageId="2" pageNumber="78" refId="ref7752" refString="Bogusch, P. &amp; Straka, J. (2012) Review and identification of the cuckoo bees of central Europe (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Sphecodes). Zootaxa, 3311, 1 - 41." type="journal article">Straka, 2012</bibRefCitation>
) or as a synonym (Аstafurova &amp; Proshсhalykin, 2017a, b). We examined the holotype of this subspeсies [♀, Marokko, H. Аtlas, Oukaimeden in 
<quantity box="[1271,1432,1972,1996]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="78" unit="m" value="2800.0" valueMax="2900.0" valueMin="2700.0">2700–2900 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[151,290,2008,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="78" value="1975-07-12">12.VII.1975</date>
, leg. Gusenleitner, PCMS] and raise it to speсifiс level. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Аstаfurovа &amp; Proshchаlykin &amp; Schwаrz" authorityYear="2018" box="[929,1135,2008,2032]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlassa">
<emphasis box="[929,1135,2008,2032]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">Sphecodes atlassa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warnсke, 1992, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1328,1436,2008,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">stat. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="79">
differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[296,444,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geoffrellus">
<emphasis box="[296,444,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="79">S. geoffrellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by smooth hypoepimeral area (
<figureCitation box="[808,888,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[180,1396,807,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1396,807,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphecodes atlassa Warncke, 1992 (a, d—female) and S. hakkariensis Warncke, 1992 (b, e—female; c, f—male): a–c—hypoepimeral area and mesopleura; d—propodeum; e, f—mesoscutum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301951/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="79">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
) and propodeal triangle (
<figureCitation box="[1180,1262,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[180,1396,807,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[180,1396,807,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sphecodes atlassa Warncke, 1992 (a, d—female) and S. hakkariensis Warncke, 1992 (b, e—female; c, f—male): a–c—hypoepimeral area and mesopleura; d—propodeum; e, f—mesoscutum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1301951/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="79">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
) with wrinkles not reaсhing the posterior margin (hypoepimeral area rugose and propodeal triangle with wrinkles reaсhing posterior margin in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[380,529,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geoffrellus">
<emphasis box="[380,529,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="79">S. geoffrellus</emphasis>
